>Do Sergals even have a certain personality usually?
This is a little complicated. The species was created for a very weird Japanese pen-and-paper RPG. However weird you're thinking it is, it's weirder. There is one specific sergal character the creator of the species made. Her name is Rain Silves. She is a warlord and a yandere, absolutely batshit, out of her mind, in love with the violence. People meme about her. She's an outlier. Among her species she is a giantess, and generally speaking sergals, despite the carnivore death-machine appearance, are not too far different, psychologically, from humans, and may even be less violent than humans, unless they're being led by a charismatic warlord like Rain Silves. In that case, >rape >rape >rape >rape >rape >rape. But they're mostly not like that, at least most of the time.

And yes, according to the one who created them, sergals are a bit dumb. Specifically she says that, as a general rule, they have a tendency to be concrete thinkers. They're not good at abstract reasoning, mathematics, puzzles, that kind of thing. They are very good at problem-solving. They can learn to speak other languages. They have a tendency to be very intuitive, to go with a gut feeling, and it mostly works for them. That having been said, there are many of them, they aren't all alike, and there are bell curve distributions of all the personality traits among them. Lyka can be an enthusiastic smart spergy goof who's really good at abstract reasoning. It's okay. They exist. She'd be less of an outlier than Rain Silves is.
